-- Al-Khodari Sons Gains Most in Week After Capital Increase Plan
-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 2012-03-03T09:06:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-03/al-khodari-sons-gains-most-in-week-after-capital-increase-plan.html
Abdullah A.M. Al-Khodari Sons Co. (ALKHODAR) 
rose the most in a week after the Saudi Arabian contracting
company announced plans to raise its capital by 25 percent.  The  shares  gained 3.7 percent, the largest intraday
increase since Feb. 25, to 55.75 riyals at 11:48 a.m. in Riyadh
after trading up at 56 riyals.  The Al Khobar, Saudi Arabia-based company plans to issue
one bonus share for every four held to raise its capital to
531.25 million riyals ($142 million) from 425 million riyals, it
said in a statement to the Saudi bourse today. The companyâ€™s
board also recommended paying a dividend of 0.5 riyals a share
for the second half.  To contact the reporter on this story:
